  "explanation": "**Step 1: Find $f(x)$.**\nUsing points $(1, 3)$ and $(4, 9)$:\n$$m_f = \\frac{9 - 3}{4 - 1} = \\frac{6}{3} = 2$$\nUsing point $(1, 3)$: $3 = 2(1) + b \\Rightarrow b = 1$.\nSo $f(x) = 2x + 1$.\n\n**Step 2: Find $g(x)$.**\nUsing points $(1, 11)$ and $(4, 2)$:\n$$m_g = \\frac{2 - 11}{4 - 1} = \\frac{-9}{3} = -3$$\nUsing point $(1, 11)$: $11 = -3(1) + b \\Rightarrow b = 14$.\nSo $g(x) = -3x + 14$.\n\n**Step 3: Form and solve $f(x) + g(x) = 6$.**\n$$f(x) + g(x) = (2x + 1) + (-3x + 14) = -x + 15$$\n$$-x + 15 = 6 \\Rightarrow -x = -9 \\Rightarrow x = 9$$\n\n**Verify:** $f(9) = 2(9)+1 = 19$ and $g(9) = -3(9)+14 = -13$. Sum $= 19 + (-13) = 6$. ✓",
